    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - BE 200, CE 200, CE 300 Model - ELECTRONIC GAUGE CLUSTER -
        DESCRIPTION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>The
                <hotlnk xrefid="f08290501">Electronic Gauge Cluster</hotlnk>
                (EGC) components include gauges, warning lamps, an alarm, a digital display, a display set/reset button,
                and a switch pack containing up to three switches.
            </para>
            <para>The EGC communicates with the electrical system controller (ESC) and other controllers connected to
                the Drivetrain 1939 data link.
            </para>
            <figure id="f08290501" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G08290501.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
                <caption>Electronic Gauge Cluster</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
    </svcsubsec>
